{"questionId":"25536","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A function, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math>, has its derivative given by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>′</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>p</mi></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi></math>. The following&nbsp;diagram shows part of the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>′</mo></math>.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/1100b7dade0b754c0f83bcdb3258dba9d472ee7a.png\"></p>\n<p>The graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>′</mo></math> has an axis of symmetry <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>q</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The vertex of the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>′</mo></math> lies on the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Sketch the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>″</mo></math>, the second derivative of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math>. Indicate clearly the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-intercept and&nbsp;the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-intercept.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"text-align:left;padding-left:120px;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/64d4e31925fe40a917396e07d6e92fa9ea1851ed.png\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><br>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for line with positive gradient, <em><strong>A1</strong>&nbsp;</em>for correct intercepts.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"25536","referenceCode":"22M.1.SL.TZ1.7d","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Sketch the graph of f″, the second derivative of f. Indicate clearly the x-intercept and the y-intercept.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.3—Graphing","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.4—Key features of graphs, intersections using technology"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}